   "source": [
    "## Exercise 1\n",
    "We download monthly data for the S\\&P 500 index (`^GSPC`) and the 13-week Treasury Bill rate (`^IRX`) from Yahoo! Finance for the period January 1, 2000 to February 28, 2026. The `^IRX` series is an annualized yield in percent, so it is converted into a monthly risk-free rate as: \n",
    "$$\n",
    "r_{f,t} = (1 + IRX_t/100)^{1/12} - 1.\n",
    "$$ \n",
    "\n",
    "Monthly excess market returns are then computed as: $\\tilde r_{m,t} = r_{m,t} - r_{f,t}$, where $r_{m,t}$ denotes the monthly return on the S\\&P 500 index. We use the estimated monthly mean excess return $\\mu_m$ and monthly variance $\\sigma_m^2$ to calibrate the synthetic asset universe. @tbl-market-moments reports the estimated monthly market moments and their annualized counterparts. The estimated monthly mean excess return is approximately 0.45\\%, corresponding to an annualized mean excess return of approximately 5.45\\%. The annualized variance is approximately 0.0228."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "ex1-market-data",
   "metadata": {
    "cache": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| label: ex1-market-data\n",
    "\n",
    "ticker = [\"^GSPC\", \"^IRX\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "prices = tf.download_data(\n",
    "    domain=\"stock_prices\",\n",
    "    symbols=ticker,\n",
    "    start_date=\"2000-01-01\",\n",
    "    end_date=\"2026-02-28\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "prices[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(prices[\"date\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "gspc = (\n",
    "    prices\n",
    "    .query('symbol == \"^GSPC\"')\n",
    "    .sort_values(\"date\")\n",
    "    .set_index(\"date\")\n",
    "    .resample(\"ME\")\n",
    "    .last()\n",
    "    .assign(r_m=lambda x: x[\"adjusted_close\"].pct_change())\n",
    "    .reset_index()[[\"r_m\"]]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "irx = (\n",
    "    prices\n",
    "    .query('symbol == \"^IRX\"')\n",
    "    .sort_values(\"date\")\n",
    "    .set_index(\"date\")\n",
    "    .resample(\"ME\")\n",
    "    .last()\n",
    "    .assign(r_f=lambda x: (1 + x[\"adjusted_close\"] / 100) ** (1 / 12) - 1)\n",
    "    .reset_index()[[\"r_f\"]]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "returns = (\n",
    "    pd.concat([gspc, irx], axis=1)\n",
    "    .assign(r_tilde_m=lambda x: x[\"r_m\"] - x[\"r_f\"])\n",
    "    .dropna()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_m = returns[\"r_tilde_m\"].mean()\n",
    "sigma2_m = returns[\"r_tilde_m\"].var(ddof=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_m_annualized = 12 * mu_m\n",
    "sigma2_m_annualized = 12 * sigma2_m\n",
    "\n",
    "summary_ex1 = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"metric\": [\"mu_m\", \"sigma2_m\", \"mu_m_annualized\", \"sigma2_m_annualized\"],\n",
    "    \"value\": [mu_m, sigma2_m, mu_m_annualized, sigma2_m_annualized]\n",
    "})"
   ]
  },
